SIMPLE: lusty
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lusty
<hw>Lust"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Lustier</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Lustiest</adjf>.]</amorph> <ety>[From <er>Lust</er>. See
<er>Lust</er>, and cf. <er>Luscious</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Exhibiting lust or vigor; stout; strong; vigorous;
robust; healthful; able of body.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Neither would their old men, so many as were yet vigorous and
<qex>lusty</qex>, be left at home.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Beautiful; handsome; pleasant.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Of large size; big.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
⟦ldquo⟧Three <xex>lusty</xex> vessels.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Evelyn.</au>
<specif>Hence, sometimes,</specif> <def>pregnant.</def> <mark>[Obs. or
Prov.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Lustful; lascivious.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lusus naturae</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
